McIntosh-Butler&rsquo;s husband has seen work dry up during the pandemic, but she&rsquo;s only going to work one more shift this week and then stay away. She&rsquo;ll wear a bandana over her face, as many workers at the facility have begun doing, even though she knows it won&rsquo;t do much.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll have my $200 check and they can have the rest,&rdquo; McIntosh-Butler says. &ldquo;I just think that it&rsquo;s too dangerous right now, because I don&rsquo;t know who I&rsquo;m coming into contact with, and HR isn&rsquo;t taking it seriously.&rdquo;
